div.summary:
W. S. Everett, secretary, and Jas. B. Orr, Pres. provide the list of
                    winners from the First Annual Fair of the Farmers and Mechanics Industrial
                    Association of Franklin County. The people listed above won in one or more of
                    the following categories: Horses--Blooded Stock (Quick Draft and Saddle Colts);
                    Carriage Horses; Saddle Horses; Brood Mares, Quick Draft; Common Horses, Heavy
                    Draft; Common Horses, Quick Draft; Team of Draft Horses--Team of Mules--Mules
                    and Jacks; Short Horned Durhams and Devons; Durham, Devon and Teeswater Mixed;
                    Common Stock; Fat Sheep; Sheep (Cotswald and Bakewell Mixed--South Down Fine
                    Wool); Swine; Products Of The Soil; Vegetables, Fruits And Flowers; Agricultural
                    Implements; Carriages, Harness; Castings; House Manufacture (2 Divisions);
                    Poultry; Bacon, Hams, Dairy And Honey; Plowing Match; Lady Equestrians;
                    Unenumerated Articles.
